The '''Cape Town Open Education Declaration''' is a major international statement on [[Open access (publishing)|open access]], [[open education]] and [[open educational resources]]. It emerged from a conference on open education hosted in [[Cape Town]] on 14 and 15 September 2007 by the [[Shuttleworth Foundation]] and the [[Open Society Institute]].<ref>{{cite web|title=OLCOS and the Cape Town Open Education Declaration|url=http://www.olcos.org/english/news-archive/cape-town-declaration.htm|work=OLCOS|accessdate=30 January 2014}}</ref> The "aim of this meeting ''[being]'' to accelerate efforts to promote open resources, technology and teaching practices in education". Individuals and organizations that sign the Declaration share its "statement of principle, a statement of strategy and a statement of commitment".<ref name="CTOED2008">[http://www.capetowndeclaration.org/read-the-declaration Cape Town Open Education Declaration]</ref>
As of January 2014, over 2,400 individuals and 250 organisations (including the [[Wikimedia Foundation]]<ref>[[wmf:Minutes/2007-12-11]]</ref>) have signed the declaration.<ref>{{cite web|title=View Signatures|url=http://www.capetowndeclaration.org/list_signatures|work=The Cape Town Open Education Declaration|accessdate=30 January 2014}}</ref>
== See also == *[[Budapest Open Access Initiative]] *[[UNESCO 2012 Paris OER Declaration]]
